{
  "name": "RPlog_Aurejin_Saves_Jessalyn",
  "title": "Aurejin Saves Jessalyn",
  "summary": "In a silent jungle ravine on Yavin near an ancient ziggurat temple, the Jedi Aurejin is sought out by the fallen, Sith-twisted Jessalyn Valios, who has been stalking his group. Convinced her only escape from the manipulation Palpatine worked on her mind is death, she begs Aurejin to destroy her, but he insists his way is redemption, not destruction. Goading her to act on her true self's will, Aurejin watches as Jessalyn turns her blaster on herself and fires; at the last instant his lightsaber flashes to deflect the killing bolt, severing only a lock of her hair. Freed and weeping, Jessalyn is comforted by Aurejin as the wary Mailyn (Raines) and the young apprentice Mira arrive. Mailyn, feeling betrayed and inconsequential, retreats into the jungle despite Aurejin's plea for trust, while Mira joyfully realizes her old friend Jessalyn has been restored. Resolving to seek healing and sanctuary, Jessalyn offers her ship and a safe haven -- the Refrain of Anshalar -- and the group sets out, leaving Aurejin shaken by the long-unheard name.",
